Ideally the RELEASE_3_20 branch should build and check  without TIMEOUT/ERROR as well as devel.  This is to ensure users on that branch have working code for their version of R since Bioconductor releases are closely associated with a version of R.   If there were changes pushed to the devel branch that fixed the code they should also be pushed to RELEASE_3_20; if not it may be intermittent or temporary that could clear up on its own.   The deadline for fixing release is this coming Monday March 31 after which the code will be frozen.


